rete intent entries. Achievable on current models at negligible compute; triggered by losing an unrecorded spoken design session.|] High Minimum Zero [prometheus gemma intent-recording speech-to-text])) (xnnb ([(Technology (Software Intelligence))] Constraint [|The intent recorder uses voice recognition as the cutoff between recorded-and-processed and ignored audio: it ignores audio not recognised as the psyche by default (filtering out the psyche's wife who shares the residence). If the active microphone passes to the wife, the recorder recognises the voice change and routes her speech to her own dynamically-spawned persona instance — captured intent belongs to her as a distinct psyche with her own intent layer.|] Medium Minimum Zero [intent-recording voice-recognition prometheus])) (arb2 ([(Technology (Software Intelligence))] Decision [|Long-term intent-recording direction: spirit-CLI-driven intent-recording-of-role for all roles, in real-time, with Prometheus running continuous capture; the chat-mediated capture pattern (psyche prompt → agent extracts → spirit-CLI record) gives way over time to direct real-time recording across every role's interaction surface.|] Low Minimum Zero [spirit-cli intent-recording prometheus roles])) (p7kn ([(Technology (Software Intelligence))] Decision [|Local AI on Prometheus: install both big Gemma multimodal models — the ~31B dense for max quality and the ~26B MoE (a4b, ~4B active/token) for fast inference — at bf16 with the f16 vision projector, and deploy multiple quantization variants as separate selectable models in the llama-server router, each named by quant in the modelId (e.g. gemma-4-26b-a4b-bf16, a 4-bit variant), sharing one mmproj per base model so the user picks quality vs speed per use. Local Pi and agent sessions can select these prometheus-hosted models as a local provider. Prefer a curated best/latest model per capability over near-duplicates (Prometheus may prefetch large candidates since memory/storage allows a